args: Aw, that was great, buddy! Nice job!\nYou've got your intro down pat.
Yeah, it means you've gotten better.\nIt's a good thing.
Goodthing. Happy then. Thank you, Ilia.
Hee hee! Ilia and Mordecai almost sound\nlike mother and son.
It's giving me flashbacks to when I was\na little girl living with my own mother.
I'm glad to see Ilia forming relationships\nwith others, but...
But his being an otherworldly life-form\nstill worries you.
Yes. There's no telling what influence an\norganism removed from this world's laws\nmight have.
What should we work on next, Mordecai?\nI'm happy to teach you whatever I know!
That is a dangerous offer, Ilia.
You know dragons dislike creatures\nwho are not of this world.
Offering one knowledge is tantamount\nto inviting it to dinner and giving it a bed.
You risk drawing the dragons' ire.
If you worry about the worst-case scenario,\nyou'd never get ANYTHING done! Sheesh!\nBesides, if they get mad, I'll deal with it.
Why must you ALWAYS be like this?!\nDo you not understand how much I\nworry about you?!
And why must YOU constantly forget that\nI'm a grown woman who doesn't need\nprotecting all the dang time?!
Now, now! Let's all take a deep breath,\ncalm down, and attempt to—
Are we under attack?! I'll go check!
What IS that charred and blackened thing?
Yeaaah, this is one of my tools for\nexperiments. Or it was, anyway.
Have you been doing dangerous\nexperiments again?
No! Do you seriously think I'd mess\nsomething this basic up?
Then who is responsible for it?
Try to imitate Ilia. But then...
Wait, you tried to perform alchemy?!
Just wanted know more about\nwhat Ilia does...
Meene right. Danger russ for me...learn.
You're AMAZING! I can't believe you\nstarted experimenting all by yourself!
Why would I be angry? This is a HUGE\nmilestone in your growth!
Growth goodthing. But if I didn't want\nlearn, not break thing.
I think you've got the wrong idea, buddy.
Gaining knowledge isn't a bad thing.\nAll that matters is what's in the heart\nof the person who learns it.
You said you conducted that experiment\nbecause you wanted to know more about\nthe stuff I was doing, right?
Well, there's nothing bad about that.\nIt's just pure curiosity!
You've done nothing wrong, and no one is\nblaming you for anything.
Knowledge belongs to everyone, my man.\nWe all have equal rights to learn.
Where you were born or what race you're\nfrom don't matter—no one's right to learn\nshould EVER be denied.
Mom, you crossed the barriers between\nfaeries and humans and taught me all\nsorts of things.
So how is that different from me\nteaching Mordecai?
Plus, teaching him about this world will\nhelp PREVENT more accidents!
You should know after raising me that\nthere's no limit to curiosity.
*sigh* Very well. You win.\nI leave Mordecai's education to you.
Thanks! ...See, Mordecai? Now you don't\nhave to feel bad about learning!
What if break Ilia things again?
Every success is built on a failure, buddy.\nThat's just how you learn.
But if you seek out the reasons for your\nfailures and let them lead you to success,\nit's all worth it in the end.
So let's study all sorts of things together.\nWhat do you say?
Thank you! Want learnmore about world!\nMuchmuch more!
